    <h1>Vegan Alfredo Sauce</h1>

    
    <h2>Ingredients</h2>
    <ul>
    
        <li>12 ounces cauliflower, broken into small florets</li>
    
        <li>1/2 cup pine nuts</li>
    
        <li>2 tablespoons olive oil</li>
    
        <li>1/2 cup water</li>
    
        <li>2 cloves garlic</li>
    
        <li>2 tablespoons lemon juice</li>
    
        <li>2 tablespoons nutritional yeast</li>
    
        <li>1 teaspoon salt</li>
    
        <li>1/2 teaspoon dijon mustard</li>
    
    </ul>
    

    
    <h2>Steps</h2>
    <ol>
    
        <li>Bring a large pot of water to a boil.</li>
    
        <li>Add the cauliflower and pine nuts and boil until cauliflower is fork-tender, about 8 minutes.</li>
    
        <li>Drain and transfer to a blender.</li>
    
        <li>To the blender add the olive oil, water, garlic, lemon 
juice, nutritional yeast, salt, mustard, and ground black pepper to 
taste.</li>
    
        <li>Blend until creamy.</li>
    
        <li>Serve with your choice of pasta, mixing in pasta cooking water if needed to reach desired consistency.</li>
    
    </ol>
    

    
